messages.content:
RECOMMENDED ORDER OF LEARNING ANY topic/framework/lib/concept:
0. Wikipedia 
1. YouTube (+Vimeo) - Introductory videos (conference talks) and introductory Podcasts on the topic
2. YouTube (+Vimeo) + Podcasts - Experience reports (conference talks on usage/experience/tips-tricks of the tech)
3. YouTube/Udemy/etc - Tutorial videos (coding)
4. Main website of the library/framework/concept
5. Reference documentations / authoritative / seminal paper of the concept
6. Main author/team's Medium/Twitter/blog/Github (follow them)
7. Main community/forum/group of the library/framework/concept
8. GitHub Issues of the project + StackOverflow
9. Articles
10. Books
11. Introduce, Explain and Guide another peer on the topic/framework/lib (which is still part  of your own learning)
12. Stay up-to-date via all update channels (YouTube, podcasts, GitHub, Twitter, Medium, blog RSS, etc.)
